14 WHEREAS, Terry Holder further served as the first head football coach at Greenbrier High
15 School, achieving records of 7-4, 9-3, and 8-3 with playoff appearances each year; and
16 WHEREAS, throughout his 30 baseball seasons and four football seasons as a head coach,
17 he experienced only one losing season, which occurred during his first year coaching football
18 at Wilkinson County High School; and
19 WHEREAS, Terry Holder has been previously inducted into three prestigious Hall of
20 Fames—the Georgia Athletic Coaches Association (GACA), the Georgia Dugout Club, and
21 the Brewton-Parker College Athletic Hall of Fame; and
22 WHEREAS, this distinguished gentleman has given inspiration to many through his high
23 ideals, morals, and deep concern for his fellow citizens, and he possesses the vast wisdom
24 which only comes through experience and the strength of character which is achieved
25 through overcoming the many challenges of life; and
26 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper that the outstanding accomplishments of this
27 remarkable and distinguished Georgian be appropriately recognized.
28 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
29 the members of this body congratulate Terry Holder upon the grand occasion of his induction
30 into the Georgia Sports Hall of Fame and extend the most sincere best wishes for continued
31 health and happiness.
32 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
33 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Terry
34 Holder.
